- 'Regions' refer to specific areas within the image;
- 'Versions' refer to different iterations or edits of the same image;
- 'Access events' refer to instances when the image was accessed or viewed;
- 'Tags' are descriptive keywords or labels that are attached to the image.

- "more than one region" implies that there are at least two regions in the image;
- "annotations mentioning 'rectangle'" means the annotation text includes the word "rectangle";
